{"id":45743,"date":"2024-01-22T09:41:00","date_gmt":"2024-01-22T04:11:00","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/?p=45743"},"modified":"2023-05-22T22:42:05","modified_gmt":"2023-05-22T17:12:05","slug":"colours-to-make-a-room-bigger-and-brighter","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/home-interiors\/colours-to-make-a-room-bigger-and-brighter\/","title":{"rendered":"What Colours Make A Room Look Bigger And Brighter"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>Make your room look bright, colourful and spacious<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>One of the easiest and most effective ways to transform the look and feel of a room is through the use of colour. Certain colours can make a room appear larger, brighter, and more inviting, while others can have the opposite effect. In this blog post, we&#8217;ll explore what colours make a room look bigger and brighter and provide tips on how to use them to create a more spacious and welcoming environment in your home.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">What Paint Colors Make Rooms Look Bigger?<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>When it comes to <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/home-interiors\/tips-to-choose-perfect-home-painting-colors\/\">choosing paint colours<\/a> that make a room look bigger, light and neutral hues are the way to go. These colours reflect light, creating the illusion of more space. Popular choices include shades of white, beige, grey, and light blue. These colours not only make a room feel larger but also provide a blank canvas for you to decorate with accents and accessories in brighter hues.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/22220328\/right-colour-choices-for-room.jpg\" alt=\"Right colour choices make your room look bigger\" class=\"wp-image-45751\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/22220328\/right-colour-choices-for-room.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/22220328\/right-colour-choices-for-room-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/22220328\/right-colour-choices-for-room-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/22220328\/right-colour-choices-for-room-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>Make your room look bigger with a smart choice of colours<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">What Colours Make a Bedroom Look Bigger?<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Consider using lighter shades of blue, green, or grey in a bedroom. These cool tones create a calming and relaxing atmosphere while making the space feel larger. You can also use accent colours, such as white or pastel shades, to add interest and contrast to the room.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/22220322\/colour-choices-for-bedroom.jpg\" alt=\" Right colour choices to make bedroom look bigger\" class=\"wp-image-45750\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/22220322\/colour-choices-for-bedroom.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/22220322\/colour-choices-for-bedroom-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/22220322\/colour-choices-for-bedroom-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/22220322\/colour-choices-for-bedroom-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>A grey wall to add an earthy touch to your room<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">What Colours Make a Small Kitchen Look Bigger?<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>White is often the go-to colour choice when making a small kitchen look bigger. White cabinets, walls, and countertops reflect light, making the space feel more open and airy. However, if you prefer more colour, consider using light grey, beige, or pale blue as a complementary shade.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/22220315\/colours-to-make-kitchen-look-bigger.jpg\" alt=\"Right choices of colours to make a kitchen look bigger\" class=\"wp-image-45749\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/22220315\/colours-to-make-kitchen-look-bigger.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/22220315\/colours-to-make-kitchen-look-bigger-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/22220315\/colours-to-make-kitchen-look-bigger-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/22220315\/colours-to-make-kitchen-look-bigger-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>Light green kitchen for a tropical vibe<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"mbgc-slide-caption\"><a href=\"#contactUsModal\" data-toggle=\"modal\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"Looking for functional and space saving home interiors?\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/08172802\/looking-for-functional-and-space-saving-home-interiors.jpg \" \/><\/a><\/div>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">What Colours Make a Living Room Look Bigger?<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Light and <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/living-room-interiors\/neutral-living-room-color-ideas\/\">neutral shades work well for a living room<\/a>, just like in other rooms. Light greys, soft blues, and pale greens are great for walls and furniture. You can also add pops of colour with accessories, such as throw pillows and rugs, to add interest and contrast to the space.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/22220309\/colours-to-make-living-room-look-bigger.jpg\" alt=\"Right choices of colours to make a living room look bigger\" class=\"wp-image-45748\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/22220309\/colours-to-make-living-room-look-bigger.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/22220309\/colours-to-make-living-room-look-bigger-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/22220309\/colours-to-make-living-room-look-bigger-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/22220309\/colours-to-make-living-room-look-bigger-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>A combination of grey and blue creates a striking contrast<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">What Colour Carpet Makes a Room Look Bigger?<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>When it comes to carpets, lighter shades are the way to go. Beige, cream, and light grey are great options for a more spacious feel. You can also use patterns to create interest and texture without overwhelming the space.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/22220302\/right-carpet-colour-to-make-room-look-bigger.jpg\" alt=\"Right carpet colour choices to make a room look bigger\" class=\"wp-image-45747\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/22220302\/right-carpet-colour-to-make-room-look-bigger.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/22220302\/right-carpet-colour-to-make-room-look-bigger-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/22220302\/right-carpet-colour-to-make-room-look-bigger-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/22220302\/right-carpet-colour-to-make-room-look-bigger-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>Choose a carpet that adds a spacious vibe to your room<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">What Colour Ceiling Makes a Room Look Bigger?<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>A white ceiling is a classic choice for making a room feel bigger. It reflects light and provides a bright and airy feel to the space. However, if you&#8217;re feeling bold, try painting the ceiling a light blue or pale green to add a bit of colour and interest to the room.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/22220256\/ceiling-colours-to-make-room-look-bigger.jpg\" alt=\"Right choice of Ceiling colours to make a room look bigger\" class=\"wp-image-45746\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/22220256\/ceiling-colours-to-make-room-look-bigger.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/22220256\/ceiling-colours-to-make-room-look-bigger-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/22220256\/ceiling-colours-to-make-room-look-bigger-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/22220256\/ceiling-colours-to-make-room-look-bigger-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>Light colour ceiling adds to the height of your room<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">What Color Furniture Makes a Room Look Bigger?<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>When it comes to furniture, the same rules apply as to paint colours. Light and neutral shades are best for creating a more spacious feel. White, beige, and light grey are great options for sofas, chairs, and tables. You can also add interest with accent pillows or throws in brighter hues.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/22220250\/furniture-colours-to-makes-room-look-bigger.jpg\" alt=\"Furniture colours to makes a room look bigger\" class=\"wp-image-45745\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/22220250\/furniture-colours-to-makes-room-look-bigger.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/22220250\/furniture-colours-to-makes-room-look-bigger-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/22220250\/furniture-colours-to-makes-room-look-bigger-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/22220250\/furniture-colours-to-makes-room-look-bigger-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>Similar toned furniture makes the room look spacious<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"mbgc-slide-caption\"><a href=\"#contactUsModal\" data-toggle=\"modal\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"End-to-end home interior solutions with functional designs\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/08172629\/end-to-end-home-interior-solutions-with-functional-designs.jpg \" \/><\/a><\/div>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">What Color Sofa Makes a Room Look Bigger?<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>A light-coloured sofa is the best choice for making a room look bigger. A white or beige sofa will reflect light and create a more open and inviting space. However, if you prefer a bit more colour, consider a light grey or pale blue sofa to add interest and contrast to the room.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/22220244\/sofa-colours-to-make-room-look-bigger.jpg\" alt=\"Sofa colours to make a room look bigger\" class=\"wp-image-45744\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/22220244\/sofa-colours-to-make-room-look-bigger.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/22220244\/sofa-colours-to-make-room-look-bigger-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/22220244\/sofa-colours-to-make-room-look-bigger-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/22220244\/sofa-colours-to-make-room-look-bigger-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>A lovely beige sofa setup\n<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Here are some of the most frequently asked questions:<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>What are some colours that make a room look bigger and brighter?<\/strong><br>Some colours that can make a room look bigger and brighter include:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><li>White: White reflects light, making a room appear larger and brighter. It also has a clean and crisp look, making the space more open.<\/li><li>Pale shades of blue and green: These colours have a calming effect and can make a room feel more serene and spacious. They also reflect light well, helping to brighten up a room.<\/li><li>Light shades of grey and beige: These colours create a neutral backdrop that can help to make a room feel more open and airy. They also pair well with other colours, making it easy to add pops of colour through accessories or artwork.<\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>How does using light colours make a room look bigger and brighter?<\/strong><br>Light colours make a room look bigger and brighter because they reflect more light than darker colours. Lighter colours also have a receding effect, creating the illusion of more space. This is because they don&#8217;t absorb as much light as darker colours, which make a room feel smaller and more enclosed.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Can dark colours be used to make a room look bigger and brighter?<\/strong><br>While dark colours can be used to create a dramatic and cosy feel in a room, they generally don&#8217;t make a room look bigger and brighter. Dark colours absorb light, making a room feel smaller and more enclosed. However, if you want to use dark colours in a small room, you can use them as an <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/bedroom-interiors\/bedroom-accent-wall-designs\/\">accent wall<\/a> or in small doses, such as through accessories or artwork.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Should I paint the ceiling a different colour to make the room look bigger and brighter?<\/strong><br>Painting the ceiling a different colour can create the illusion of height in a room, making it feel bigger and more spacious. However, this technique is best used in rooms with high ceilings. If your room has a standard ceiling height, painting the ceiling a different colour may make the room feel disjointed and choppy. It&#8217;s generally better to stick with a light colour on the ceiling to help reflect light and create the illusion of more space.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>What about using bold or bright colours in a small room?<\/strong><br>Using bold or <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/home-interiors\/bright-room-colours\/\">bright colours in a small room<\/a> can work, but using them strategically is important. Too much bold colour can make a small room feel overwhelming and cluttered. Instead, try using bold colours as accents, such as through throw pillows, curtains, or a statement piece of furniture. This can add visual interest and personality to a room without overwhelming it. Additionally, using bright white or light colours on the walls can help balance bold accents and make the room feel brighter and more spacious.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>In conclusion, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/home-interiors\/tips-to-choose-perfect-home-painting-colors\/\">using the right colours<\/a> can make a big difference in how spacious and inviting a room feels. If you have any further questions or want expert designers to help you with some functional interiors for your home, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/contact-us\/\">book a free consultation<\/a> with us today.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"row blog-form\">\n\t<div class=\"offset-lg-3 col-lg-6 bg-light\">\n<fieldset class=\"field-set\">\n<!-- <legend align=\"left\"> -->\n                    \n    <h3 class=\"widget-title text-dark text-center mb-0\">Looking For Functional Interior Designs?<\/h3>\n  \n \n     <p class=\"text-center text-dark mt-0\"> Get 20% extra space with smart solutions<\/p>\n    <!-- <\/legend> -->\n<form id=\"blogContactUsFormMain\" action=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/get_quote_action.php\" method=\"post\"\n    novalidate=\"novalidate\">\n    <div class=\"form-group\">\n        <input type=\"text\" class=\"form-control\"  name=\"your-name\" placeholder=\"Enter your name*\" \/>\n        <!-- <span class=\"sales-txt-label\" id=\"labeltxt\">Enter your name*<\/span>  -->\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"form-row dc-falg-row\">\n        <!-- <div class=\"form-group col-md-3 guideForm\">\n            <select name=\"your-phone-ext\" id=\"id_select2_example\" class=\"id_select2_example drop-downfield form-dropdown\"\n                onfocus='this.size=5;' onblur='this.size=1;' onchange='this.size=1; this.blur();'\n                data-width=\"100%\" data-minimum-results-for-search=\"Infinity\">\n               \n                <option value=\"+01\"\n                    data-img_src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/10\/06163948\/01.png\">\n                    +01\n                <\/option>\n                <option value=\"+91\"\n                    data-img_src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/10\/06164015\/91.png\"\n                    selected>\n                    +91\n             